title: Personal Spending in the month of March - DIARY 3(~ 5 minutes)
description: The purpose of this study is to examine people's spending over the course of a month in their lives. In this study we will ask you to tell us about your spending plans for the month of March. We will also ask you questions about your personal situation (e.g., income), your personality and attitudes, and about strategies you use to help you achieve your spending plans.    This study includes an intake survey (~10 minutes) and we will also ask for your permission to contact you for 10 diary surveys throughout the course of the month (~5 minutes each), as well as a final diary report at the end of the month (~5 minutes).  For the intake survey, you will earn US $0.50. For each of the 10 diary reports, you will earn US $0.50 per report (10 x $0.50 = $5.00). For the final report, you will earn US $1.00. The final diary report will be sent on March 31st. Thus, you can earn up to US $6.50 in this study.  Your participation as well as your responses will be strictly confidential, only the researchers will have access to the data (see a list of people who are involved with this study below). At the end of the study, we will destroy all information that was used to contact you for the diary survey and compensation (i.e., MTurk worker identification numbers).   People involved in this study: Johanna Peetz (faculty member), Mariya Davydenko (PhD student). This study has received clearance by the Carleton University Research Ethics Board - B (# 111530).

title: Building mental health resilience in the COVID-19 pandemic.(~ 20 minutes)
description: Interested in improving your mood? Fill out brief surveys and get a chance to watch informative videos teaching you skills to help you feel better! title: Personal Spending in the month of March - DIARY 3(~ 5 minutes)
description: The purpose of this study is to examine people's spending over the course of a month in their lives. In this study we will ask you to tell us about your spending plans for the month of March. We will also ask you questions about your personal situation (e.g., income), your personality and attitudes, and about strategies you use to help you achieve your spending plans.    This study includes an intake survey (~10 minutes) and we will also ask for your permission to contact you for 10 diary surveys throughout the course of the month (~5 minutes each), as well as a final diary report at the end of the month (~5 minutes).  For the intake survey, you will earn US $0.50. For each of the 10 diary reports, you will earn US $0.50 per report (10 x $0.50 = $5.00). For the final report, you will earn US $1.00. The final diary report will be sent on March 31st. Thus, you can earn up to US $6.50 in this study.  Your participation as well as your responses will be strictly confidential, only the researchers will have access to the data (see a list of people who are involved with this study below). At the end of the study, we will destroy all information that was used to contact you for the diary survey and compensation (i.e., MTurk worker identification numbers).   People involved in this study: Johanna Peetz (faculty member), Mariya Davydenko (PhD student). This study has received clearance by the Carleton University Research Ethics Board - B (# 111530).

If these criteria are not met after the first four questions, the survey will automatically end and you will not be compensated. Once you submit the survey, we will evaluate your responses. We will contact you in a few days if you are qualified to take part in the main study.

title: Depression and Self-Help (DaSH) Study - Session 1 HIT(~ 20 minutes)
description: This is a continuation HIT of the DaSH Study, which is a multi-part longitudinal study. This study includes multiple online tasks and waves of data collection broken up into various HITs. Each HIT will take a different amount of time to complete and will pay a different amount as well. See the section titled “Session 1 HIT” below for more details about this particular HIT…We are Anthony Papa, Ph.D. and Emerson Epstein, M.A. at the University of Nevada, Reno studying how to improve depression online (IRB Study ID Number: 1577013). If you join, you will be asked to complete several psychological measures before being offered a FREE self-help program. The self-help program is a cognitive-behavioral program delivered online and designed to help you improve your depression. title: Depression and Self-Help (DaSH) Study - Week 7 Assessment HIT(~ 2 minutes)
description: This is a continuation HIT of the DaSH Study, which is a multi-part longitudinal study. See the section titled “Week 7 Assessment HIT” below for more details about this particular HIT…We are Anthony Papa, Ph.D. and Emerson Epstein, M.A. at the University of Nevada, Reno studying how to improve depression online (IRB Study ID Number: 1577013). There are a total of five sessions to be completed within a month, with each session including material to read, tasks to complete online, and exercises to practice offline. You will also be asked to complete up to five assessments of depression throughout the whole study. To make sure you are eligible for this study, see the “Qualifications Required” section below.

title: Depression and Self-Help (DaSH) Study - Session 4 HIT(~ 20 minutes)
description: This is a continuation HIT of the DaSH Study, which is a multi-part longitudinal study. This study includes multiple online tasks and waves of data collection broken up into various HITs. Each HIT will take a different amount of time to complete and will pay a different amount as well. See the section titled “Session 4 HIT” below for more details about this particular HIT…We are Anthony Papa, Ph.D. and Emerson Epstein, M.A. at the University of Nevada, Reno studying how to improve depression online (IRB Study ID Number: 1577013). If you join, you will be asked to complete several psychological measures before being offered a FREE self-help program. The self-help program is a cognitive-behavioral program delivered online and designed to help you improve your depression. There are a total of five sessions to be completed within a month, with each session including material to read, tasks to complete online, and exercises to practice offline. You will also be asked to complete up to five assessments of depression throughout the whole study. To make sure you are eligible for this study, see the “Qualifications Required” section below.

title: Depression and Self-Help (DaSH) Study - Session 2 HIT(~ 20 minutes)
description: This is a continuation HIT of the DaSH Study, which is a multi-part longitudinal study. This study includes multiple online tasks and waves of data collection broken up into various HITs. Each HIT will take a different amount of time to complete and will pay a different amount as well. See the section titled “Session 2 HIT” below for more details about this particular HIT…We are Anthony Papa, Ph.D. and Emerson Epstein, M.A. at the University of Nevada, Reno studying how to improve depression online (IRB Study ID Number: 1577013). If you join, you will be asked to complete several psychological measures before being offered a FREE self-help program. The self-help program is a cognitive-behavioral program delivered online and designed to help you improve your depression. There are a total of five sessions to be completed within a month, with each session including material to read, tasks to complete online, and exercises to practice offline. You will also be asked to complete up to five assessments of depression throughout the whole study. To make sure you are eligible for this study, see the “Qualifications Required” section below.

title: Depression and Self-Help (DaSH) Study - Session 5 HIT(~ 22 minutes)
description: This is a continuation HIT of the DaSH Study, which is a multi-part longitudinal study. This study includes multiple online tasks and waves of data collection broken up into various HITs. Each HIT will take a different amount of time to complete and will pay a different amount as well. See the section titled “Session 5 HIT” below for more details about this particular HIT…We are Anthony Papa, Ph.D. and Emerson Epstein, M.A. at the University of Nevada, Reno studying how to improve depression online (IRB Study ID Number: 1577013). If you join, you will be asked to complete several psychological measures before being offered a FREE self-help program. The self-help program is a cognitive-behavioral program delivered online and designed to help you improve your depression. There are a total of five sessions to be completed within a month, with each session including material to read, tasks to complete online, and exercises to practice offline. You will also be asked to complete up to five assessments of depression throughout the whole study. To make sure you are eligible for this study, see the “Qualifications Required” section below.

title: Depression and Self-Help (DaSH) Study - Session 3 HIT(~ 22 minutes)
description: This is a continuation HIT of the DaSH Study, which is a multi-part longitudinal study. This study includes multiple online tasks and waves of data collection broken up into various HITs. Each HIT will take a different amount of time to complete and will pay a different amount as well. See the section titled “Session 3 HIT” below for more details about this particular HIT…We are Anthony Papa, Ph.D. and Emerson Epstein, M.A. at the University of Nevada, Reno studying how to improve depression online (IRB Study ID Number: 1577013). If you join, you will be asked to complete several psychological measures before being offered a FREE self-help program. The self-help program is a cognitive-behavioral program delivered online and designed to help you improve your depression. There are a total of five sessions to be completed within a month, with each session including material to read, tasks to complete online, and exercises to practice offline. You will also be asked to complete up to five assessments of depression throughout the whole study. To make sure you are eligible for this study, see the “Qualifications Required” section below.

title: Depression and Self-Help (DaSH) Study - Session 3 HIT(~ 22 minutes)
description: This is a continuation HIT of the DaSH Study, which is a multi-part longitudinal study. This study includes multiple online tasks and waves of data collection broken up into various HITs. Each HIT will take a different amount of time to complete and will pay a different amount as well. See the section titled “Session 3 HIT” below for more details about this particular HIT…We are Anthony Papa, Ph.D. and Emerson Epstein, M.A. at the University of Nevada, Reno studying how to improve depression online (IRB Study ID Number: 1577013). If you join, you will be asked to complete several psychological measures before being offered a FREE self-help program. The self-help program is a cognitive-behavioral program delivered online and designed to help you improve your depression. There are a total of five sessions to be completed within a month, with each session including material to read, tasks to complete online, and exercises to practice offline. You will also be asked to complete up to five assessments of depression throughout the whole study. To make sure you are eligible for this study, see the “Qualifications Required” section below.
